<br>
First .. get a map<br>
<br>
At level 10, hunt at the Shadeweaver's Thicket zoneline.  Get a friendly druid or wizzard to lesser succor/evac you there.<br>
<br>
At level 13 or when the mobs all turn green, head over to the Hollowshade side.  Just invis up and go.  Hunt near the Hollowshade zoneline .. bugs are your friend here!!  Get your pet up and go for the little ones first.  Root the bugs and keep them rooted .. they hit hard!<br>
<br>
If you can get a group going, go after the fiends, but I would not suggest you solo them.  An enchanter is a great addition to a fiend group as they will mob you.  I haven't tried charming them yet as I've been in good groups that didn't need the help.<br>
<br>
After you tire of the fiends and are about level 16 or so .. head for the ShadowHaven zoneline and get into a bandit group there.<br>
<br>
I leveled my Bard from 13 to 20 in one weekend .. about 10 hours of play.<br>
<br>
I got my enchanter from level 14 to level 15 last night in about 1 hour<br>
<br>
Good luck!<br>
